race.comment: BEEARETEE (2) finished in the minor money at his last three outings and shouldn't have a problem stretching out to the 1700m today. Caught the eye from last on the turn with a handy third over 1300m at Ballina. Genuine top-three contender. TURPIN'S TORMENT (7) gets in light again after jumping in trip with an unlucky second over the mile at Tamworth. Found form last start and don't dismiss. REDADEL (4) went back from the wide gate and never looked a threat with a plugging seventh over 1900m at Armidale. Gets a better set-up with the claim. Improver. SOME GIRLS (12) jumps quickly in trip at her third run back and will appreciate Farr's claim again. Finds a more suitable contest and can turn things around.
